parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the 3.3L engine can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The engine makes abnormal noises
such as knocking
rattling
or ticking sounds; the vehicle stalls or loses power; the check engine light illuminates; the vehicle goes into limp mode; oil consumption increases; the engine seizes or catches fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed Recall Repair for Hydraulic Brake System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to repair the hydraulic brake system in a timely manner can lead to a increased risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities due to malfunctioning brakes.
symptoms: None reported
as the complaints are related to the delay in receiving the recall repair
not the symptoms of the faulty brake system.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unavailability of Parts for Recall Repair
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for the recall repair can lead to a delay in fixing the safety issue, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: None reported
as the complaints are related to the unavailability of parts
not the symptoms of the faulty brake system.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Anti-Lock Brake System (ABS) Module
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS module can cause an electrical short, leading to a fire risk, even when the vehicle is parked.
symptoms: None reported
as the complaint is related to the recall notice and the failure of the manufacturer to remedy the issue in a timely manner.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column/steering wheel connection can cause the steering wheel to become loose, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose
makes a popping noise
and produces a jerking motion when turning; the steering wheel sticks in one position and jerks when trying to adjust; the steering wheel exhibits "stiction" after driving for 20-30 minutes
becoming worse at higher speeds; small movements of the wheel produce no steering effect
but resistance is felt; the steering feels like it "freezes" until a minimum break-out force is applied
resulting in an overshoot past the intended point.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the steering system can cause the vehicle to become unstable, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The steering becomes unstable during windy days
overcompensating for wind and becoming scary to drive; the steering wheel seems to stick in one position and jerk when trying to adjust the steering in the slightest.
